body:
I was watching over videos on youtube of URF, and I realized that when it comes to this &#039;Sandbox Mode&#039;, Riot kind of has it already.  No resource usage, minimal cooldowns, if URF was available to use making custom matches against bots, it might actually fill the need players have for a way to practice mechanics.  

Can&#039;t nail that Insec?  Take Lee Sin into URF and practice, over and over and over.  Struggling to land your skillshots?  Take your champ into URF and practice against bots.  There&#039;s probably a lot more to it than I think there is, but I think having URF available at any time to play vs bots would really fill a void that League needs.  An efficient way to practice without having to endure the salty players in Normals while you learn.  Little less &#039;Oh great, we got a first time Anivia, GG&#039; and more &#039;Oh, so I land that ability and then this one does more damage?&#039;  

Pls Rito.  I&#039;m Bronze for a reason.  I suck at this game and I want to improve, but there&#039;s nowhere to practice effectively and I think URF actually provides an ideal environment for it.
